SIMPLE: losing
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Losing
<hw>Lo"sing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Losenger</er>.]</ety> <def>Given to flattery or deceit; flattering;
cozening.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Amongst the many simoniacal that swarmed in the land, Herbert,
Bishop of Thetford, must not be forgotten; nick-named <qex>Losing</qex>,
that is, the Flatterer.</q> <rj><qau>Fuller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Losing</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Losing
<hw>Los"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Lose</er>,
<pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <def>Causing or likely to cause a loss; <as>as,
a <ex>losing</ex> game or business; a <ex>losing</ex>
strategy</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Who strive to sit out <qex>losing</qex> hands are lost.</q>
<rj><qau>Herbert.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Losingly</ent>⟦br⟧
